  "text": "Vertical root fractures are, in general, a contraindication to root canal treatment; especially those extending down into the middle and apical part of the root. [CITATION_1] Very often these generate a localised periodontal pocket along their length with subsequent loss of marginal bone. It is important to check for isolated pockets in teeth being assessed for root canal treatment.",
